      <solution>
        <p>
          <ol>
            <li>
              <p>
                We are given the angular speed is
                <m>\omega=25</m> revolutions per minute.
                To convert our angular speed to radians per minute,
                we use the fact that one revolution is <m>2\pi</m> radians to get
                <me>
                  \omega=25\frac{\mbox{revolution} }{\mbox{minute} }=25\frac{\mbox{rev} }{\mbox{minute} }\cdot2\pi\frac{\mbox{radians} }{\mbox{revolution} }=50\pi\frac{\mbox{radians} }{\mbox{minute} }
                </me>
                Thus the hoe uli is moving at an angular speed of <m>50\pi</m> radians per second.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Since the radius is <m>r=2</m> ft and the angular speed is
                <m>\omega=180</m> is measure in radians per minute we can <xref ref="def_linear-speed">Definition</xref> to calculate the linear speed
                <me>
                  v=r\omega=2\mbox{ft} \cdot50\pi\frac{\mbox{rad} }{\mbox{min} }\cdot\frac{\mbox{mile} }{5280\mbox{ft} }\cdot\frac{60\mbox{min} }{\mbox{hr} }\approx3.57\frac{\mbox{miles} }{\mbox{hour} }
                </me>
                Thus the steersperson moving the hoe uli at a linear speed of 3.57 mph.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </p>
      </solution>
